        <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" expanded="false" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:anchor>1197</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">def-001M</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>def-001M.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Symmetric and Antisymmetric Part">Symmetric and Antisymmetric Part</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:authors></fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Any square matrix <fr:tex display="inline">A</fr:tex> can be written as the sum of a symmetric and antisymmetric matrix:
    <fr:tex display="block">         A = A_S + A_A     </fr:tex>
    where <fr:tex display="inline">A_S</fr:tex> is the <fr:strong>symmetric part</fr:strong> and <fr:tex display="inline">A_A</fr:tex> is the <fr:strong>antisymmetric part</fr:strong>.
    <fr:tex display="block">         A_S = \frac {1}{2}(A + A^T)     </fr:tex>
    where <fr:tex display="inline">A_S</fr:tex> is a <fr:link type="local" href="def-001N.xml" addr="def-001N" title="Symmetric Matrix">symmetric matrix</fr:link>
    <fr:tex display="block">         A_A = \frac {1}{2}(A - A^T)     </fr:tex>
    where <fr:tex display="inline">A_A</fr:tex> is an <fr:link type="local" href="def-001O.xml" addr="def-001O" title="Antisymmetric Matrix">antisymmetric matrix</fr:link></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter></fr:backmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter></fr:backmatter>
